In an effort to improve the housing needs of people, government has approved N4.892 billion for the construction of 1,000 housing units in Adamawa state. The  state Commissioner for Information and Strategy, Dr Umar Garba-Pella, announced the development shortly, after the state executive council meeting  Wednesday in Yola. According to him, the houses to be located in Yola, would comprises 3-bedrooms and 2-bed room respectively. “The council approved that the project should take off immediately. “A total sum of N4.892 billion is earmarked for the project; 1,000 housing units in Yola.” He said that about 14 construction firms were successful in the bidding processes and would build 350 three-bedrooms units and 650 two-bedroom units, respectively. Pella said that the project was in demonstration of the government’s commitment to ensuring that the citizens would have access to affordable houses. Government had earlier inaugurated the construction of 2000 units. The breakdown involved 1,300 units in Malkohi in Yola-South, 400 in Jimeta, Yola-North and 300 in Mubi-North and South LGAs of the state. The contract was awarded to Family Homes Limited to be completed in 12 months, as  confirmed by  Mr Femi Adefale, Managing Director of the company at the flag-off event last year in September. 